Kelvin Ekerete Anthony Nwakaeme, has received a €100,000 bonus from Trabzonspor after contributing 19 goals to the team this season. The Nigerian activated the clause in his contract after scoring 11 goals and providing eight assists this season in 31 games across all competition. The former Hapoel Be’er Sheva forward has contributed eight goals and six assists in the league this season to help the team move top of the table. The 29-year-old also took home the €100,000 bonus after scoring 11 goals and 10 assists for the team last season. Nwakaeme was on target in their 2-0 away win at Genclerbirligi on Friday. The forward will be instrumental to the team in their next couple of games after a red card to star striker Alexander Sorloth. Since joining the Turkish club from Isreali side Hapoel Be’er Sheva in 2018, the Nigerian has scored 22 goals and contributed 16 assists. Copyright PUNCH.
